-rating-star-5 wprm-rating-star-full" data-rating="5" data-color="#D3A0C1" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-label="Rate this recipe 5 out of 5 stars" onmouseenter="window.WPRecipeMaker.userRating.enter(this)" onfocus="window.WPRecipeMaker.userRating.enter(this)" onmouseleave="window.WPRecipeMaker.userRating.leave(this)" onblur="window.WPRecipeMaker.userRating.leave(this)" onclick="window.WPRecipeMaker.userRating.click(this, event)" onkeypress="window.WPRecipeMaker.userRating.click(this, event)" style="font-size: 1em;"><svg width="16px" height="16px" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path fill="none" stroke="#D3A0C1" stroke-width="2" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M11.99,1.94c-.35,0-.67.19-.83.51l-2.56,5.2c-.11.24-.34.4-.61.43l-5.75.83c-.35.05-.64.3-.74.64-.11.34,0,.7.22.94l4.16,4.05c.19.19.27.45.22.7l-.98,5.72c-.06.35.1.7.37.9.29.21.66.24.98.08l5.14-2.71h0c.24-.13.51-.13.75,0l5.14,2.71c.32.16.69.13.98-.08.29-.21.43-.56.37-.9l-.98-5.72h0c-.05-.26.05-.53.22-.7l4.16-4.05h0c.26-.24.34-.61.22-.94s-.4-.58-.74-.64l-5.75-.83c-.26-.03-.48-.21-.61-.43l-2.56-5.2c-.16-.32-.48-.53-.83-.51,0,0-.02,0-.02,0Z"/></svg></span><div class="wprm-recipe-rating-details wprm-block-text-normal"><span class="wprm-recipe-rating-average">4.95</span> from <span class="wprm-recipe-rating-count">191</span> votes</div></div></div></div><div class="post-header__action-wrapper"><div><a class="post-header-button" href="#wprm-recipe-container-134594"><svg width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true" role="img" focusable="false"><use href="#utility-arrow-down-large"></use></svg>Jump to Recipe</a><a class="post-header-button" href="#wpforms-353020">Email Recipe</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="site-inner" id="main-content"><div class="content-area"><main class="site-main" role="main"><article class="type-post"><div class="entry-content"><div class="shared-counts-hidden-image-container" style="display:none;"><img width="500" height="1000" decoding="async" src="https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/SP-Crispy-Fried-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-.jpg" class="shared-counts-hidden-image" data-pin-description="Fried pickles are the best snack for anyone who loves a little salty crunch with plenty of dill flavor. This recipe starts with tangy pickle slices coated in a light batter, then breaded with Panko crumbs and fried until golden and crispy. They’re perfect with ranch dip or a zesty sauce and make a great side dish for chicken or burgers. Whether you make them as chips or spears, these fried pickles are a crowd-pleaser for parties and gatherings. #spendwithpennies" data-pin-media="https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/SP-Crispy-Fried-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-.jpg" alt="" /></div>
<p class="has-text-align-left">Fried pickles are a fun, crispy snack just like you’d find at the county fair. This easy version makes crispy fried pickles with a quick batter and crunchy panko. Serve them warm with ranch for dipping, or pile them onto burgers for extra crunch.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%201800'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="basket of Crispy Fried Pickles with pickles on the side" class="wp-image-357147" title="Fried pickles are a crowd-pleasing recipe that combines tangy dill slices with a golden, crunchy coating. The batter and crumb combo make each bite perfectly crisp and flavorful. Dip them into ranch dip or spicy sauce, or serve them on the side with chicken tenders or sandwiches. You can make them into spears for a bigger bite of dill pickle or chip-style for easy snacking. Fried pickles are the best snack for parties, game nights, or anytime cravings hit. #spendwithpennies" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/1200-Crispy-Fried-Pickles-SpendWithPennies.jpg 1200w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/1200-Crispy-Fried-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-500x750.jpg 500w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/1200-Crispy-Fried-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/1200-Crispy-Fried-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/1200-Crispy-Fried-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/1200-Crispy-Fried-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-400x600.jpg 400w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/1200-Crispy-Fried-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-350x525.jpg 350w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/1200-Crispy-Fried-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-270x405.jpg 270w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/1200-Crispy-Fried-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-165x248.jpg 165w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/1200-Crispy-Fried-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-580x870.jpg 580w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/1200-Crispy-Fried-Pickles-SpendWithPennies.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" src="https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/1200-Crispy-Fried-Pickles-SpendWithPennies.jpg" alt="basket of Crispy Fried Pickles with pickles on the side" class="wp-image-357147" title="Fried pickles are a crowd-pleasing recipe that combines tangy dill slices with a golden, crunchy coating. The batter and crumb combo make each bite perfectly crisp and flavorful. Dip them into ranch dip or spicy sauce, or serve them on the side with chicken tenders or sandwiches. You can make them into spears for a bigger bite of dill pickle or chip-style for easy snacking. Fried pickles are the best snack for parties, game nights, or anytime cravings hit. #spendwithpennies" srcset="https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/1200-Crispy-Fried-Pickles-SpendWithPennies.jpg 1200w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/1200-Crispy-Fried-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-500x750.jpg 500w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/1200-Crispy-Fried-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/1200-Crispy-Fried-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/1200-Crispy-Fried-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/1200-Crispy-Fried-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-400x600.jpg 400w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/1200-Crispy-Fried-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-350x525.jpg 350w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/1200-Crispy-Fried-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-270x405.jpg 270w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/1200-Crispy-Fried-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-165x248.jpg 165w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/1200-Crispy-Fried-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-580x870.jpg 580w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>
<div class="aff-disc"><p class="affiliate-disclosure">This post may contain affiliate links. Please read our <a href="https://www.spendwithpennies.com/disclosure-and-privacy-policy/">disclosure policy</a>.</p></div>


<div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="block-tip-border">

<div class="wp-block-group block-tip-border__header is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading block-tip-border__title" id="h-holly-s-recipe-highlights">Holly&#8217;s Recipe Highlights</h2>
</div>



<ul class="wp-block-list is-style-gamma">
<li><strong>Flavor</strong>: Tangy dill pickles with a light, golden Panko crust for the ultimate crunch in every bite.&nbsp;</li>



<li><strong>Skill Level:</strong> Intermediate. This recipe requires shallow frying and attention to oil temperature for the best results.</li>



<li><strong>Prep Note:</strong> For the best crunch, dry the pickles first, fry them in batches, and keep them warm in the oven for easy serving.</li>



<li><strong>Serving Suggestions:</strong> Serve crispy deep-fried pickles right away with your favorite dips like <a href="https://www.spendwithpennies.com/light-buttermilk-ranch-dressing-dip/">buttermilk ranch dressing</a>, <a href="https://www.spendwithpennies.com/blue-cheese-dressing/">blue cheese dressing</a>, or <a href="https://www.spendwithpennies.com/aioli/">homemade aioli</a>.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>

</div></div>



<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1798" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%201798'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Ingrediets to make crispy fried dill pickles labeled: salt &amp; pepper, paprika, milk, egg, baking powder, panko breadcrumbs, flour, and dill pickles" class="wp-image-358529" title="Fried pickles are the ultimate crunchy snack, made with juicy dill pickle slices and a crispy golden coating. This recipe uses a batter and Panko crumb crust to give every bite a delicious crunch. Pair them with ranch dip, spicy sauce, or even serve them with chicken sandwiches or burgers. For more dill flavor, make them into spears or pickle chips for easy dipping. Fried pickles are the best appetizer to share with family and friends. #spendwithpennies" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/IG-Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies2.jpg 1200w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/IG-Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies2-500x749.jpg 500w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/IG-Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies2-800x1199.jpg 800w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/IG-Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies2-768x1151.jpg 768w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/IG-Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies2-1025x1536.jpg 1025w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/IG-Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies2-400x599.jpg 400w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/IG-Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies2-350x525.jpg 350w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/IG-Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies2-270x405.jpg 270w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/IG-Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies2-165x248.jpg 165w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/IG-Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies2-580x870.jpg 580w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/IG-Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies2.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1798" src="https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/IG-Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies2.jpg" alt="Ingrediets to make crispy fried dill pickles labeled: salt &amp; pepper, paprika, milk, egg, baking powder, panko breadcrumbs, flour, and dill pickles" class="wp-image-358529" title="Fried pickles are the ultimate crunchy snack, made with juicy dill pickle slices and a crispy golden coating. This recipe uses a batter and Panko crumb crust to give every bite a delicious crunch. Pair them with ranch dip, spicy sauce, or even serve them with chicken sandwiches or burgers. For more dill flavor, make them into spears or pickle chips for easy dipping. Fried pickles are the best appetizer to share with family and friends. #spendwithpennies" srcset="https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/IG-Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies2.jpg 1200w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/IG-Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies2-500x749.jpg 500w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/IG-Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies2-800x1199.jpg 800w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/IG-Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies2-768x1151.jpg 768w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/IG-Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies2-1025x1536.jpg 1025w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/IG-Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies2-400x599.jpg 400w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/IG-Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies2-350x525.jpg 350w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/IG-Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies2-270x405.jpg 270w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/IG-Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies2-165x248.jpg 165w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/IG-Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies2-580x870.jpg 580w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-ingredient-notes">Ingredient Notes</h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list is-style-default">
<li><strong>Pickles:</strong> Use dill pickles for a classic flavor and crunch. Spicy, sour, or garlic pickles make fried pickles into a new recipe every time. For the best results, choose a thicker pickle and pat them dry before coating for a good crunch. Thin slices won’t hold up or give that bold pickle bite in every piece.</li>



<li><strong>Breading</strong>: A quick batter helps the crumbs stick to the pickles, especially after a short 5-minute rest. <a href="https://www.spendwithpennies.com/panko-bread-crumbs/">Panko</a> gives the crispiest crunch, and dried dill adds a flavor boost.</li>
</ul>


<div class="block-tip-border has-icon"><div class="block-tip-border__icon has-primary-background-color"><svg width="44" height="44" aria-hidden="true" role="img" focusable="false"><use href="#category-appetizers-and-snacks"></use></svg></div>

<div class="wp-block-group block-tip-border__header is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading block-tip-border__title" id="h-prep-the-pickle">Prep the Pickle</h2>
</div>



<ul class="wp-block-list is-style-alpha">
<li>Best for classic fried pickles: <strong>pickle chips (rounds)</strong>.</li>



<li>Best for big pickle flavor: <strong>spears</strong> (fry a little longer).</li>



<li>Best for burgers or sandwiches: <strong>long slices (sandwich-style cuts)</strong>.</li>
</ul>

</div>


