<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-how-to-make-fried-pickles">How to Make Fried Pickles</h2>



<ol class="wp-block-list is-style-alpha">
<li>Combine batter ingredients <strong>(full recipe below) </strong>and let it rest for about 5 minutes.</li>



<li>Pat pickle slices dry, dip each piece in the batter, then into the breadcrumbs.</li>



<li>Fry in hot oil until both sides are golden brown. </li>
</ol>



<p>Serve warm with your favorite dipping sauces.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%201800'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="cooked Crispy Fried Dill Pickles on a baking sheet" class="wp-image-249714" title="Fried pickles are a crispy, crunchy snack that’s loaded with dill pickle flavor and the perfect golden bite. This recipe coats tangy pickle slices in a seasoned batter, then covers them in Panko crumbs for the best crunch. Serve them hot with ranch dip or your favorite sauce for snacking, game day, or even a fun side with chicken. Try pickle spears for even more dill in every bite or chips for easy dipping. However you make them, these fried pickles are sure to be a hit. #spendwithpennies" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-5.jpg 1200w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-5-400x600.jpg 400w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-5-165x248.jpg 165w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-5-500x750.jpg 500w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-5-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-5-700x1050.jpg 700w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-5-350x525.jpg 350w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-5-270x405.jpg 270w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-5-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-5-96x144.jpg 96w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-5.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" src="https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-5.jpg" alt="cooked Crispy Fried Dill Pickles on a baking sheet" class="wp-image-249714" title="Fried pickles are a crispy, crunchy snack that’s loaded with dill pickle flavor and the perfect golden bite. This recipe coats tangy pickle slices in a seasoned batter, then covers them in Panko crumbs for the best crunch. Serve them hot with ranch dip or your favorite sauce for snacking, game day, or even a fun side with chicken. Try pickle spears for even more dill in every bite or chips for easy dipping. However you make them, these fried pickles are sure to be a hit. #spendwithpennies" srcset="https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-5.jpg 1200w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-5-400x600.jpg 400w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-5-165x248.jpg 165w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-5-500x750.jpg 500w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-5-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-5-700x1050.jpg 700w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-5-350x525.jpg 350w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-5-270x405.jpg 270w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-5-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Crispy-Fried-Dill-Pickles-SpendWithPennies-5-96x144.jpg 96w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>


<div class="block-tip-border has-icon"><div class="block-tip-border__icon has-primary-background-color"><svg width="44" height="44" aria-hidden="true" role="img" focusable="false"><use href="#category-tips-and-ideas"></use></svg></div>

<div class="wp-block-group block-tip-border__header is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow">
<h2 class="wp-block-heading block-tip-border__title" id="h-holly-s-helpful-hints">Holly&#8217;s Helpful Hints</h2>
</div>



<ul class="wp-block-list is-style-alpha">
<li>Keep panko dry by adding ½ cup to the small bowl at a time, and refilling as you go.</li>



<li>Choose a neutral oil with a high smoke point, like vegetable oil or canola oil. </li>



<li>Fry in small batches and use a heavy-bottomed pot so the oil temp stays steady and the coating stays crisp.</li>



<li>If the coating slips, the pickles were likely too wet, or the crumbs got damp. Pat dry and use fresh panko to recoat them.</li>



<li>Reheat leftover deep-fried dill pickles in an <a href="https://www.spendwithpennies.com/crispy-air-fryer-dill-pickles/">air fryer</a> or place them under the broiler until they crisp up.</li>
</ul>

</div>

