				<ol class="comment-list">
					<li id="comment-484825" class="comment even thread-even depth-1 parent">
			<article id="div-comment-484825" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
												<b class="fn">Patricia Landry</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://www.spendwithpennies.com/crispy-fried-dill-pickles/comment-page-6/#comment-484825"><time datetime="2026-01-22T07:00:38-08:00">January 22, 2026 at 7:00 am</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Can you use the air fryer instead of oil? Thank you for all the great recipes.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-484825" data-commentid="484825" data-postid="65953" data-belowelement="div-comment-484825" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Patricia Landry" aria-label="Reply to Patricia Landry">Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
		<ol class="children">
		<li id="comment-484901" class="comment byuser comment-author-spend-with-pennies-ao odd alt depth-2 staff">
			<article id="div-comment-484901" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
												<b class="fn">Spend With Pennies AO</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://www.spendwithpennies.com/crispy-fried-dill-pickles/comment-page-6/#comment-484901"><time datetime="2026-01-23T09:05:51-08:00">January 23, 2026 at 9:05 am</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Absolutely! These can be air fried at 400°F for about 10-12 minutes. Flip them after 5 minutes.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-484901" data-commentid="484901" data-postid="65953" data-belowelement="div-comment-484901" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Spend With Pennies AO" aria-label="Reply to Spend With Pennies AO">Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
		</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li id="comment-479335" class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
			<article id="div-comment-479335" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
												<b class="fn">Kelly</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://www.spendwithpennies.com/crispy-fried-dill-pickles/comment-page-6/#comment-479335"><time datetime="2025-10-20T11:39:58-07:00">October 20, 2025 at 11:39 am</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>These were so good! The only thing I didn&#8217;t do was to sprinkle them with salt, and I was glad I didn&#8217;t. I used Claussen pickles and I find them already salty enough. I had a ton of batter left over, so next time I&#8217;ll 1/2 that part of the recipe. Thanks for another keeper recipe!<img class="wprm-comment-rating" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAP///wAAACwAAAAAAQABAEACAkQBADs=" data-lazy-src="https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-recipe-maker/assets/icons/rating/stars-alt-5.svg" alt="5 stars" width="80" height="16" /></p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-479335" data-commentid="479335" data-postid="65953" data-belowelement="div-comment-479335" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Kelly" aria-label="Reply to Kelly">Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
		</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li id="comment-466044" class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1">
			<article id="div-comment-466044" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
												<b class="fn">Chaz</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://www.spendwithpennies.com/crispy-fried-dill-pickles/comment-page-6/#comment-466044"><time datetime="2024-12-23T21:19:46-08:00">December 23, 2024 at 9:19 pm</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Nicely Done! Ty for sharing, I will keep this bookmark for when the next time i am Thirsty for more!<img class="wprm-comment-rating" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAP///wAAACwAAAAAAQABAEACAkQBADs=" data-lazy-src="https://www.spendwithpennies.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-recipe-maker/assets/icons/rating/stars-alt-5.svg" alt="5 stars" width="80" height="16" /></p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

